http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/New-dairy-project-for-STs/article14000896.ece

Minister for Welfare of Scheduled Tribes P.K. Jayalakshmi will inaugurate a State-level dairy project of the Scheduled Tribe Development Department at Mananthavady in the district at 2 p.m. on Saturday.The project, to be executed through Milma, aims at empowering tribal families in Palakkad, Malappuram, and Wayanad districts. The Scheduled Tribe Development Department has sanctioned Rs.6.4 crore to Milma for the project.FeaturesHybrid cows, cattle sheds, fodder, assistance of veterinary experts would provided for free to Paniya and Adiya tribesmen of Sulthan Bathery and Mananthavady taluks in Wayanad district and other tribal sects in Attappady and Nilambur taluks, in Palakkad and Malappuram districts respectively, under the project. Free insurance will also be provided.Earlier projectThe project is modelled on the lines of a dairy project launched by the department with Milma for 46 tribal families of the Sugandhagiri cardomom project in the district in 2014-15 fiscal at a cost of Rs.2.33 crore.The success of that project prompted the department to extend the project, Scheduled Tribe Development Department sources said.